        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-12-21 15:38:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI am not clear on what that flag setting to false actually does?",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "2f2a09cf03d027fc7aaa20335915a46d76086d7a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 879,
          "name": "subhash kumar singh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "subh.singh@samsung.com",
          "username": "subhash_singh"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-12-21 17:21:15.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\n> (1 comment)\n > \n > I am not clear on what that flag setting to false actually does?\n\nHello Steve, thanks for your comment.\n\nFor e.g.\n\nnode_templates:\n    SOTNConnectivity:\n      ...\n      properties:\n        colorAware:\n          get_input: sotnconnectivity_colorAware   //GetInput\n\nThis node parsed as GetInput node for Property.getValue(), if 2nd arg is false.\nOtherwise it will come as null and it will be completly resolved using\nservice inputs.\n\ne.g.\ntopology_template:\n  inputs:\n    sotnconnectivity_colorAware:\n      type: boolean\n      description: The colorAware of the SOTN connectivity. Only for Ethernet type\n      required: false",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "cb4ab745a51c5529641bca88bb9214103cc87045",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 63,
          "name": "Steve Smokowski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ss835w@att.com",
          "username": "SteveSmokowski"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-12-21 17:50:59.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8: -Code-Review\n\nWhat is the reason to disable this?",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "333059e5952d2c6a344b3086a692a7a380bae220",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 879,
          "name": "subhash kumar singh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "subh.singh@samsung.com",
          "username": "subhash_singh"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-12-21 18:38:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\n> What is the reason to disable this?\n\nas part of service input we pass \n\n{\n service {\n   ....\n   ...\n     requestInputs\":{\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_eir\":\"0\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_cir\":\"100000\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_endTime\":\"2018-8-8 10:00\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_ebs\":\"200\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_startTime\":\"2018-8-1 10:00\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_dualLink\":\"true\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_reroute\":\"false\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_cbs\":\"100\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_name\":\"vpn1\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_SLS\":\"\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_description\":\"some description\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_couplingFlag\":\"true\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_colorAware\":\"true\",\n                \"sotnconnectivity0_COS\":\"standard\"\n            }\n   }\n\nso this key is specified as value of GetInput node in service.yaml.\n\nproperties:\n        colorAware:\n          get_input: sotnconnectivity_colorAware\n\nthis name is important for us to resolve the service input from UUI.\nIf we dont pass 2nd parameter then we will lose this name and it will be resolved to value.",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
